\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid10552624\charrsid10552624 C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid11163955 hancellor (VC)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid10552624\charrsid10552624 . Financially attractive. Moved to North Wales. Department then frag
mented, lacked research culture. VC hoped to develop urban sociology, had signed up to Third European}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid11163955  Poverty Programme, and moved Robert}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid10552624\charrsid10552624  onto Management Committee. But being on committee prevented him from applying for research grants. Proved impossible t
o research on local black community, a bad experience lasting seven years. Wrote a book on this but unpublishable. Programme a fiasco. Had to return \'a3120,000 from grant when ended in 1996.
\par Instead researched on proposed move of Customs and Excise VAT from Southend to Liverpool, who wanted to recruit from local black community. But move never happened. Published brief book, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\i\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid10552624\charrsid10552624 Positive Action in Action}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid10552624\charrsid10552624 
, on problems of poverty and entry to labour market.
\par Spent last five years helping department and teaching. Developed work in North Wales on race equality with older people, which could carry on after retirement. Editing official documents to make them understandable.
\par Has always felt obligation to public. Relating private experience to the wider world is central to
 task of sociologist. But should stay dispassionate and intellectual, willing to make unpopular comments and correct misleading views. A public role, but not partisan.
\par VC was keen to reach out with research to black community in Liverpool 8, living next to
 University. Few local black students or even cleaners. But difficult, because local black leadership hostile, telling people not to be interviewed by academics, saying University exploitative, untrustworthy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid11163955 , only self-interested. Robert}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid10552624\charrsid10552624  personally attacke
d for earning royalties from books. Later a retired railwayman described local leadership as \lquote the damp course\rquote , suppressing wider knowledge of people\rquote 
s aspirations and absorbing themselves much of funding intended for the community. Leadership had originated from Toxteth riots, but professionalised themselves, living off the victim status of the community, unwilling to move forward. 
\par Situation hard to deal with. As local fieldwork proved impossible, took up statistical analysis. Joined Radical Statistics Gr
oup. Took course on logistic regression. Believes in life-long education. Produced deprivation atlas for Flintshire County Council. Earlier work for Grampian Region.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\ul\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid10552624\charrsid10552624 Retirement}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid11163955  
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid10552624\charrsid10552624 Still an active sociologist, dabbling and making sense in different fields. In
terests in Crusades, and in Islamic contribution to science. His long interest in astronomy. Excavating for archaeology. Scanty data on which to build theory: similar intellectual challenge of cosmology \endash 
 and sociology. Interest in radio from father and Navy. Courses on meteorology; weather forecasting.
\par Worst things: none, although some bad periods, feels has been very lucky, his whole life a highlight.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid10552624 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid4157606\charrsid10552624 Best things: commanding a ship at sea; knowing Worsley, Rex, McLeod; wife and children. Fundamental identity is as a sociologist.

